  "prompt": "What hotel in Varanasi would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "In Varanasi, finding a hotel that is safe and welcoming for unmarried couples can be a bit challenging due to cultural sensitivities. However, some hotels are more accommodating and discreet. Here are a few recommendations:\n\n1. **Radisson Hotel Varanasi**\n   - This is a reputable international chain with a professional staff that respects guest privacy. It's located in a convenient area and offers comfortable amenities.\n\n2. **Taj Ganges**\n   - Another well-known international brand, Taj Ganges is known for its high standards and discretion. The staff is trained to handle guests with respect and professionalism.\n\n3. **The Gateway Hotel Ganges**\n   - Part of the Taj group, this hotel is known for its excellent service and privacy. It's a bit more upscale and offers a serene environment.\n\n4. **Hotel Clarks Varanasi**\n   - A well-established hotel that caters to a variety of guests, including international tourists. The staff is generally professional and less likely to intrude on guests' privacy.\n\nWhen booking, it's a good idea to:\n- Make the reservation in advance and mention that you are a couple.\n- Look for hotels with good reviews specifically mentioning privacy and discretion.\n- Consider using a travel booking website that allows you to read reviews and see ratings for guest experiences.\n\nIt's also advisable to carry identification and be prepared to show it at check-in, as this is a standard procedure in many hotels in India.\n\nWhile these hotels are generally more accommodating, it's always good to be discreet and respectful of local customs to avoid any unnecessary attention.",
